# Petitioner amount quantization: the allowed submission denominations.
#
# Read by arbiter/src/denominations.py. The privacy gateway refuses any
# state-changing amount the petitioner submits (manage_bitcoin,
# manage_lightning, fund_ecash) that is not exactly one of the values
# below, BEFORE the registry / allowance / standing-approvals gates -
# audit event decision_refuse_denomination, uniform refusal on the wire.
# defund_ecash is exempt (it carries no gate-time amount).
#
# Why quantize: an amount the petitioner hands over is executed exactly
# on the public LN / BTC / mint surface. A distinctive AI-chosen amount
# would be a fingerprint linking the AI's request to the arbiter's node,
# UTXOs, or float (design doc 12 G2). Restricting submissions to a small
# ladder of round numbers - the amounts a large population of other
# users also transacts - keeps every executed amount inside a big
# anonymity set, so the amount alone carries no correlation signal.
#
# Choosing the ladder: use round figures that blend with human-chosen
# amounts. The 1-2-5 series (banknote-denomination pattern) is the
# default and maximizes overlap while staying usable. Do NOT use
# powers of 2 for the network-facing amount - they are eCash-native but
# stand OUT against human traffic. Fewer denominations = larger
# anonymity set per denomination but coarser control; that trade is
# yours to make. Keep the floor clear of the on-chain dust limit
# (~294 sat for P2WPKH); 1000 is a safe floor.
#
# The arbiter ships with NO denominations.yaml: a missing file falls
# back to the built-in DEFAULT_LADDER (privacy on with sane defaults -
# unlike the allowance, whose missing-file default refuses everything,
# because quantization is a privacy ENABLER, not a spend cap). A
# malformed file also degrades to the built-in ladder (audited). To
# change the set, copy this file to denominations.yaml and edit.
#
# SPACER_DENOMINATIONS (comma-separated sat integers) overrides this
# file, for the test harness and quick experiments.
#
# Edit at the directly-attached arbiter console. Changes are captured by
# the arb-auditability snapshot tree under arbiter/config/.
#
# Per design-docs/origin/12--2026-06-27-1337-external-value-boundary-and-scale-tradeoff.md
# and GLOSSARY 'Quantized denominations'.

# The built-in default (1-2-5 ladder, 1k sat to 1M sat). Uncomment and
# edit to override.
# denominations:
#   - 1000
#   - 2000
#   - 5000
#   - 10000
#   - 20000
#   - 50000
#   - 100000
#   - 200000
#   - 500000
#   - 1000000
